Lombok @With doesn&#39;t support inherited fields.
However, I did find passable a workaround using the `@SuperBuilder(toBuilder = true)` annotation on both classes. This way, instead of calling the `someInstance.withSomeField(xyz)` method, 
you call a `someInstance.toBuilder().someField(xyz).build()`. 
This does preserve all of base class fields and creates a new instance. While being longer, it still looks pretty clear and self documenting code.
consider this example:

    @Data
	@SuperBuilder(toBuilder = true)
	public static class Animal {
		String color;
	}

