According to RFC 4180: 

Sec 2.6:  &quot;Fields containing line breaks (CRLF), double quotes, and commas should be enclosed in double-quotes.&quot;

Sec 2.7:  &quot;If double-quotes are used to enclose fields, then a double-quote appearing inside a field must be escaped by preceding it with another double quote&quot;

So, if `String line = &quot;equals: =,\&quot;quote: \&quot;\&quot;\&quot;,\&quot;comma: ,\&quot;&quot;`, all you need to do is strip off the extraneous double quote characters.

