&gt; My blob needs to be deleted after 1 minute &amp; How can I set the expiration of a blob?

You can use the [MS-Dcoument](https://learn.microsoft.com/en-us/azure/storage/blobs/storage-quickstart-blobs-java?tabs=powershell,managed-identity,roles-azure-portal,sign-in-azure-cli#upload-blobs-to-a-container) to upload the file from the local environment to Azure storage. To set an expiration, you need **`hierarchical namespace-enabled`** storage accounts.

In my environment, I uploaded a file with the name **`goodone.jpg`** in my container. 

**Portal:**

![enter image description here](https://i.imgur.com/oN7Y7Yi.png)

You can use the below code to set expiration with the **`Rest API`** process using Java.

**Code:**

     public static void main(String[] args) throws Exception {
            String url = &quot;https://&lt;Storage account name &gt;.blob.core.windows.net&quot;;
            String containerName = &quot;test&quot;;
            String blobName = &quot;goodone.jpg&quot;;
            String SAStoken = &quot;sp=w&amp;st=2023-12-06T07:02:08Z&amp;se=2023-12-06T15:02:08Z&amp;spr=https&amp;sv=2022-11-02&amp;sr=b&amp;sig=xxxxxx&quot;; //write permission
            Instant now = Instant.now();
    
            HttpClient httpClient = HttpClient.newBuilder()
                    .version(HttpClient.Version.HTTP_1_1)
                    .connectTimeout(Duration.ofSeconds(10))
                    .build();
                    
    
            HttpRequest request = HttpRequest.newBuilder()
                    .PUT(HttpRequest.BodyPublishers.noBody())
                    .uri(URI.create(url + &quot;/&quot; + containerName + &quot;/&quot; + blobName + &quot;?comp=expiry&amp;&quot; + SAStoken))
                    .header(&quot;x-ms-version&quot;, &quot;2020-02-10&quot;)
                    .header(&quot;x-ms-expiry-time&quot;, &quot;60000&quot;) //one minute
                    .header(&quot;x-ms-expiry-option&quot;, &quot;RelativeTonow&quot;)
                    .header(&quot;x-ms-date&quot;, now.toString())
                    .build();
    
            HttpResponse response = httpClient.send(request, HttpResponse.BodyHandlers.ofString());
    
            if (response.statusCode() == 200) {
                System.out.println(&quot;Expiry Time added to the blob successfully&quot;);
            } else {
                System.out.println(&quot;Error: &quot; + response.statusCode() + &quot; - &quot; + response.body());
            }
        }


